flowRoot.flowPara: Eclipse IDE with its plugins ecosystem
Eclipse is an open source community whose projects are focused on providing an extensible development platform and application frameworks for building soft-ware.
Requirements will be specified as textual use cases written in natural language (English). We employ readily available tools for natural language processing.
An already developed prototype implementation will be used to transform natural language to formal model that should signi-ficantly simplify your work.
The EMF project is a modeling framework and code generation facility for building tools and other applications based on a structured data model.
Once the requirements are formally captured by a meta-model, further transformation can be applied.
We are working on a project that bridges the gap between vague texts and formal models. Our project offers a substantial research potential in the domain of software engineering.
Don't waste your time implementing yet another webshop. Join our team and create something useful and interesting.
